Policy.acknowledgement_statement: Funding support for the Synergizing Genome Sequencing with Advances in Patient Reported Outcomes (PRO) study was provided by the National Institute of Nursing Research (R01NR015259). The dataset(s) used for the analyses described in this manuscript were obtained from the database of Genotypes and Phenotypes (dbGaP) found at http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gap through dbGaP accession number XXXX. Genotype and associated phenotype data for the Synergizing Genome Sequencing with Advances in Patient Reported Outcomes (PRO) study were provided by Principal Investigator Andreas Beutler, MD.

ConsentGroup.Use-Restriction:
Use of the data must be related to Cancer. Use of the data is limited to not-for-profit organizations.
Use of data is limited to any study related to cancer, allowing studies related to any cancer type and to any symptom or complication of cancer or cancer treatment such as (but not limited to), cancer fatigue, neuropathy, or other medical complications, signs, or symptoms occurring in patients with cancer or undergoing cancer treatment.
